(25, 1, 4, 'self-assess-your-competencies', 'y', 'webpage', '{embed="structure/header" use_my_placement_css=''yes''}\n\n<h2>Think about this Practice Placement Cycle &amp; Plan for Your Next Placement</h2>	\n<div class=''contrast''>\n	<p><strong>My Learning Journey Milestones</strong>\n	<img id=''fast-wheelchair'' src="/img/racer.jpg"/>\n	</p>\n	<p>Based on your learning objectives below, note what you have learned.\n	You can also use the {evidencing-matrix-link} as a guide.</p>\n	\n	<ol><li>Self assessing can be completed during or after your practice placement, or both.</li>\n	<li>Before evidencing your competencies consider:\n	<ul><li>What you have learned and how you have developed</li>\n	<li>How you have fulfilled your learning objectives</li>\n	<li>Any areas for improvement</li>\n	</ul>\n	</li>\n	<li>Check your {summary_page_link} to reflect on your past self-assessments to gauge your development</li>\n	<li>You can also check your {learning-contract-link} for this practice placement.</li>\n	</ol>\n	\n	\n	<p style=''margin-left: 1em''><label for=''revisedStrengthsStatement''><strong>What I did to fulfil my learning objectives.</strong></label>\n	<textarea id=''revisedStrengthsStatement'' data-tag=''self-assess-statement-1''></textarea></p>\n	\n	<p style=''margin-left: 1em''><label for=''learnedStatement''><strong>What I''ve learnt about myself from this practice placement. How I can improve.</strong></label>\n	\n	<textarea id=''learnedStatement'' data-tag=''self-assess-statement-2''></textarea></p>\n	\n	<p style=''margin-left: 1em''><label for=''improvementStatement''><strong>What I know now about myself as a professional. How have my strengths as an O.T. developed?</label><br>\n	<textarea id=''improvementStatement'' data-tag=''self-assess-statement-3''></textarea></p>\n	\n	<p style=''margin-left: 1em''><label for=''reflectStatement''><strong>Now, using the answers above, reflect on this Practice Placement Cycle to help you prepare for, \n	and apply what you have learned to your next Practice Placement Cycle.</strong></label><br>		\n  	<textarea id=''reflectStatement'' data-tag=''self-assess-statement-5'' style=''min-height: 120px''></textarea><br>\n\n	</p>\n	\n	<p><a href=''/practice-placement/summary-of-your-competencies/'' class=''button'' id=''continue''>Save &amp; Complete</a></p><br clear=''all''/>\n	<div style=''float:right''><em>All saved content will be saved to {eportfolio-link}</em></div>\n</div>\n\n{embed="structure/footer" js_file=''{segment_2}.js'' login_required=''true''}', '', 1378289377, 1, 'n', 0, '', 'n', 'n', 'o', 1636),
(26, 1, 4, 'evidence-your-competencies', 'y', 'webpage', '{embed="structure/header" use_ot_evidencing_css=''yes''}\n{if logged_in}\n<h2>Self-Assess Your OTCEM</h2>\n<div class=''feedback''>\n<p>\n    Here you self-assess your competency by ticking the OTCEM competency statements have achieved. This will save to your ePortfolio.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Your Practice Educator will verify your self-assessment by agreeing or disagreeing. This is Observable Evidence.\n</p>\n<p>\n    <strong><a href=''/pages/important-otcem-info'' style=''color: red !important''>Click here for IMPORTANT INSTRUCTIONS &amp; INFORMATION for Self-Assessing Your OTCEM</u>\n    . You MUST read this information first.</a></strong>\n</p>\n<p>\n    <a href="https://otca.net.au/pages/evidencing-matrix">More information about the OTCEM.</a>\n</p>\n</div>\n<div class=''evidencing-app''>\n			{exp:channel:entries channel="evidencing_matrix" limit="10" orderby="title" sort="asc" dynamic="no"}\n				<p>{text_body}</p>\n			{/exp:channel:entries}	\n		</div>\n\n{embed="structure/footer" login_required=''true''}\n\n{exp:matrix:studentjavascript \n	id=''add_evidence'' \n	jquery-selector=''.evidencing-app''\n	legend-title=''Self-Assessment/Verification Legend''\n	legend-current=''Current Verified Competencies''\n	legend-previous=''Previously Verified Competencies''\n	legend-waiting=''Self-Assessed Competencies Awaiting Verification''\n	legend-colors="FFB510, 852C8A, 1BBFE0"\n	step-label=''View the OTPP Step''\n}\n	<p>\nTick the competency statements that you have achieved then    <a href="#" id=''save_otcem''>click here to SAVE and upload to “Your ePortfolio”</a>.\n</p>\n<p>\n    Then get your Practice Educator to verify your self-assessment.\n</p>\n<p>\n    You can also use the Save window to upload Documented Evidence – this is either a description or a piece of hard/documented evidence that supports your\n    ticked self-assessment.\n</p>\n<p>\n    <strong>\n        You DO NOT have to add an individual piece of Documented Evidence (description or hard evidence) for EACH ticked competency statement. Consult the\n        Course Guide/Outline for your University Occupational Therapy Course for details on how much evidence is required. Check the Important Instruction\n        Information link in the box above for further information about this.\n    </strong>\n</p>\n<p>\nSee further information about how to self-assess and evidence your competence using the OTCEM in the    <strong>Important Instruction Information link box</strong> above.\n</p>\n<p>\n  	<a href="/docs/Occupational%20Therapy%20Competency%20Development%20Levels%20&%20Levels%20of%20Evidence.pdf">Levels of Evidence &amp; Types of Evidence</a>\n</p> \n{/exp:matrix:studentjavascript}\n<script>\n$(document).ready(function() {\n	$(''.feedback'').append("<p><a class=''button'' id=''continue'' href=''/practice-placement/summary-of-your-competencies''>Continue to your ePortfolio &rarr;</a></p>");\n});\n</script>\n{if:else}\n	{redirect=''/member/login''}\n{/if}', '', 1380671929, 1, 'n', 0, '', 'n', 'n', 'o', 2459),
